Biography


Michael R. Ward is an Professor of Economics at the University of Texas at Arlington. Previously, he was an Associate Professor at the University of Texas at Arlington and he held Assistant and Associate Professor positions at the University of Illinois and served as a staff economist at the Federal Trade Commission. He earned his doctorate and masters degrees in Economics from the University of Chicago and his bachelors in economics and mathematics from UCLA. He has taught economic core and field courses at the undergraduate, masters and doctorate levels. His research interests are in competition, innovation, and technology demand, especially in telecommunications, E-commerce and pharmaceuticals. His research has been published in a variety of peer reviewed economics journals and he has presented his research at the FCC, FTC, Department of Justice, Canadian Competition Tribunal, and the Illinois Commerce Commission as well as at numerous academic and policy forums. 




