ECON 5315-001
Competition, Innovation & Strategy
Prepares students with the skills to assess the competitive landscape in dynamic industries. Presents economic theories and provides applications that demonstrate main concepts. Key decisions for products to be analyzed include: Knowledge Production, Competition and Innovation, Intellectual Property, Applications to Computers, Communications, and Pharmaceuticals, Product Information Disclosure, Employee Performance Measurement and Incentives, Assessing Organizational Structure.


