Michael R. WardTrial Attorney at McCandlish Holton MorrisLocationRichmond, Virginia AreaIndustryLegal ServicesCurrentMcCandlish Holton MorrisPreviousMorris & Morris, P.C., McGuireWoods, Michael R. Ward, Esq.EducationTulane University Law SchoolWebsitesCompany Website342 connectionsView Michael R.’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Michael R.’s Full ProfileSummaryMy goal is always to advocate zealously on behalf of my clients to obtain the best results possible for them. I represent corporations, individuals, business owners, employers, insurance companies, financial institutions, local governments, and manufacturers. My practice primarily focuses on civil litigation in the areas of commercial litigation, products liability, tort defense, professional liability, employment law, and trade secrets. I regularly practice in all state and federal courts in Virginia.My extensive trial experience includes 43 civil jury trials, 25 civil bench trials, 6 arbitrations in state and federal courts, as well as 3 criminal bench trials. I have handled numerous appeals including oral arguments before the Virginia Supreme Court, US Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit, and the Louisiana Supreme Court. I have also successfully resolved many cases through mediation at significant cost savings for my clients. Since 2011, I have been consistently listed in The Best Lawyers in America for work in personal injury litigation defense and for product liability litigation defense. I hold the AV Preeminent Peer Review Rating for the highest level of professional excellence from Martindale-Hubbell. I have also been included in Super Lawyers for civil litigation defense since 2010. My wife and I are active members of our community. We have three sons who keep us busy.ExperienceDirectorMcCandlish Holton MorrisDecember 2016  –  Present (8 months)Richmond, Virginia AreaI currently serve as a Director in the firm's Litigat